Additional Details: Rajdhani Express trains were introduced in the year 1969 for providing high-speed connections up to 140 kilometers speed from New Delhi to the various state capital cities of India. The speed varies depending upon the particular track section.This also was the first group of trains with all its coaches being air-conditioned. Passengers are served complimentary meals during the journey.
